Omololu Ogunmade and Onyebuchi Ezeigbo in Abuja *Osinbajo, Oshiomhole are deputy chairmen *Amaechi DG, Mamora Deputy DG *Dangote, Otedola among members of special advisory committee By Omololu Ogunmade in Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari is the Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential campaign council, the presidency disclosed this on Friday. The council, according to a release by the media adviser to the President, Mr. Femi Adesina, has APC National Leader, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, as co-chairman. According to the release, Vice President Yemi Osinbajo and National Chairman of APC, Adams Oshiomhole are vice chairmen while the Minister of Transport, Rotimi Amaechi and Senator Olorunnimbe Mamora are Director-General and Deputy-General respectively. Also, two notable businessmen, Aliko Dangote and Femi Otedola, were appointed members of the 7-member Special Advisory Committee to the President. Below is the full list as released by the presidency: APC ANNOUNCES MEMBERS OF PRESIDENTIAL CAMPAIGN COUNCIL 2019 The All Progressives Congress, APC, has released the names of members of its Presidential Campaign Council for the 2019 elections. They are as follows: CHAIRMAN
